<div class="container"><section class="py-5"><h1 class="font-weight-bolder text-center text-capitalize text-dark font-family-san-serif font-size-3pt5rem px-3">Fuel Mix</h1></section><section class="py-3 case-study-left-padding pull-left"><div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12 col-xl-12 pull-left" style="float: inherit;"><section data-stellar-background-ratio="0.5" data-vc-full-width="true" data-vc-full-width-init="true"><p>A supplier’s fuel mix shows the sources of the electricity that it supplies to its customers e.g. coal, gas, nuclear and renewables.</p><p>Over the course of a year, energy suppliers must purchase sufficient electricity to feed into the national electricity grid to cover the amount their customers consume. At the end of each year, suppliers must disclose their fuel mix to the electricity and gas regulator, Ofgem. This information is published annually to help consumers make informed choices about their electricity supplier.</p><p>For further information on the impact of the UK average fuel mix&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fuel-mix-disclosure-data-tables">-fuel-mix-disclosure-</a></p><p>For further information on the health and environmental impact of coal, gas and nuclear see:</p><p>– Coal (toxic air pollution):&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ukhealthalliance.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/UK-Health-Alliance-A-Breath-of-Fresh-Air-Final-Report.pdf">-UK-Health-Alliance-</a></p><p>– Gas (emits CO<sub>2</sub>):&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar5/wg3/ipcc_wg3_ar5_chapter7.pdf">-ipcc-assessment-report-</a></p><p>– Nuclear (radioactive waste):&nbsp;<a href="https://ukinventory.nda.gov.uk/about-radioactive-waste/how-is-radioactive-waste-produced/">-radioactive-waste-</a></p></section><section data-stellar-background-ratio="0.5" data-vc-full-width="true" data-vc-full-width-init="true"><h5>WE’RE 100% RENEWABLE</h5><p>A supplier’s fuel mix shows the sources of the electricity that it supplies to its customers. Over the course of a year, energy suppliers must purchase sufficient electricity to feed into the national electricity grid to cover the amount their customers take out. At the end of each year, suppliers must disclose their fuel mix to the electricity and gas regulator, Ofgem. This information is published annually to help consumers make informed choices about their electricity supplier.</p><p>Symbio Energy believes in making a difference. The way we use our resources today, will leave an impact on our future generations. As an accountable energy provider, Symbio Energy believes in minimizing our carbon footprint and hence we offer 100% renewable energy. Doing your bit to go Green is now easy, Choose Symbio Energy!</p></section></div></section></div>

